ua.foxminded.dao

Class DAOFiller

  • java.lang.Object
    • ua.foxminded.dao.DAOFiller

  • public class DAOFiller
extends java.lang.Object
    Fills the table 'Racers' upon SQL queries with racers id, name, team, start time, end time and lap time. Takes data from resources files to fill id, name, team, start time and end time data. This methods throw FileNotFoundException if the files doesn't exist in the resource folder. Takes data from database to fill lap time. And also all methods throw DAOException if the connection to the database fails.
    Author:
    Daria Bogush

      • updateValues

        public void updateValues(java.lang.String fileStart,
                         java.lang.String fileEnd)
                  throws java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                         ua.foxminded.dao.DAOException
        Updates start, end, lap time by id upon SQL query.

        Updates start data from start.log into the database upon SQL query to count lap time.

        Updates end data from end.log into the database upon SQL query to count lap time.

        Updates lap time counted before as different between start and end data from the database that then can be displayed as racers results.

        Parameters:
        fileStart - should contain racers abbreviation and start date and time.
        fileEnd - should contain racers abbreviation and end date and time.
